description:
We had a perfect meal at Delfina. PERFECT! This has happened only 2-3 other times in my lifetime. 

Grilled Fresh Calamari w/canellini; 
Fresh Cured Anchovies Nostrano--off Pier 45 that day, apparently, w/radish cucumber salad; 
Baked Bellwether Jersey Ricotta--baked in fig leaf accompanied by some zucchini dish and toast w/tomato; 
Tomato Soup, with only 4 ingredients--the best I've ever had; 
Shortrib Cappelletti - ridiculously good; 
Rosemary Tagliatelli w/duck gizzards; 
Service - excellent.

I can't wait to go back--but at the same time afraid to b/c I know this meal will be hard to live up to.
